"```sql\nSELECT \n    ph.Id AS PostHistoryCount,\n    p.LastEditDate\nFROM \n    posts p\nJOIN \n    postHistory ph ON p.Id = ph.PostId\nWHERE \n    p.Title = 'What is the best introductory Bayesian statistics textbook?';\n```\n\nThis SQL query retrieves the count of post history entries and the last edit date for a post with the specified title. It joins the `posts` and `postHistory` tables using the `PostId` foreign key relationship and filters the results based on the post title."